[{"id":"VR188571","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Assume that Larry spends his entire allowance on the purchase of pretzels and ice-cream cones. The price of a bag of pretzels is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"$1\"><math alttext=\"$1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">$</mi><mn>1</mn></math></span></span>, and the price of an ice-cream cone is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"$2\"><math alttext=\"$2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">$</mi><mn>2</mn></math></span></span>. At his current consumption combination, the marginal utility of pretzels is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"20\"><math alttext=\"20\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>20</mn></math></span></span> and of ice-cream cones is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"60\"><math alttext=\"60\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>60</mn></math></span></span>. To maximize his utility, Larry should</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR188571_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">buy more of both goods</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">buy less of both goods</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">buy more pretzels and fewer ice-cream cones</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">buy fewer pretzels and more ice-cream cones</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">maintain his current consumption level</p>"],"answer":3}]